results.description:
White Rock lake, upper spillway 
Photo 1: There was a young one-legged gull on the spillway. It is the one with its wings up. The odd looking gull to the left is a Franklin gull in non-breeding plumage. 
Photo 2: The one-legged gull is a first winter ring-billed gull. The brown speckles on its body and wings along with the black tip on the end of the bill, no ring yet, lets you know its age. It flew towards me. 
Photo 3: You can see the stump of the missing leg at this angle. It seemed to be doing just fine. A coot got in this shot.
